# ImageMagick mjpegtools netpbm are for image support
# mjpegtools not currently compiling

   version stable 0.7.1 0.7.0 0.6
   require ImageMagick curl libXtst libcdio netpbm xine-lib
  optional lirc '' --disable-lirc for infra-red remote control support
  category video/dvd video/player
 attribute x11
    source $SOURCEFORGE_URL oxine/oxine/$VERSION/oxine-$VERSION.tar.gz
  homepage http://oxine.sf.net
  estimate 1000
      desc 'oxine is a OSD-based, on screen display, xine frontend.
oxine is a lightweight, purely OSD-based xine frontend
for set-top boxes and home entertainment systems.
It uses the on screen display functionality
of xine to display its user interface elements
like buttons, lists, sliders, and so on.
Due to this, oxine can easily use any
video output device the xine library provides.'
